# Normalize line endings. Flywheel ships shell scripts that run inside Linux
# containers and is developed across macOS/Linux/WSL; a CRLF checkout (e.g.
# cloned with Git-for-Windows' default core.autocrlf=true onto /mnt/c, then
# run in WSL) breaks `bash` with `\r` errors. Force LF for everything
# text-like, and pin scripts explicitly as belt-and-suspenders.
* text=auto eol=lf

*.sh    text eol=lf
*.bash  text eol=lf
Dockerfile* text eol=lf

# Treat common binary assets as binary so they're never line-ending munged.
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.gif   binary
*.ico   binary
